Reopening of the Jewish Museum in #Belgium: 'The tragic events of May 24th have created a huge shock in our country'
'We have all been deeply upset. What happened this sad day is a trauma that haunts us'
'If we are gathered here, it is first of all to pay homage to the four victims of the abominable slaughter'
'It is also to support their families, friends and loved ones. We show them our deep solidarity and all our friendship '
'We can not be more vandaag ook samen om een ​​sterke boodschap van standvastigheid en hoop uit te dragen'
'Elke keer als men iemand aanvalt omwille van zijn geloof, dan is het heel eleven maatschappij die wordt aangevallen'
'All behavior, all anti-Semitic or racist acts must be vigorously denounced, prosecuted and punished'
'As for calls to hatred or violence, wherever they come from, they must be repressed with the utmost firmness'
Belgium has strengthened and will further intensify international cooperation. to better fight networks / individuals threatening our democracies'
'14 / 09 is from Europese dag van de Joodse cultuur: from gelegenheid om het uitzonderlijke cultural patrimonium van de Joden te vieren '
'More than ever, it's important to be able to contrast intelligence with stupidity, humanism with hatred, wisdom with violence'
'The reopening of your museum, the reopening of our museum, is the most beautiful answer of the light on the darkness'
'Ik wil alle burgers van ons land uitnodigen om een ​​bezoek te brengen aan dit museum'
'Come visit the Jewish Museum of #Belgium, in tribute to Myriam, Emmanuel, Dominique and Alexandre and their memory'
'Let's show together that culture is stronger than hate, democracy + stronger than terror, humanity + stronger than barbarism'
